cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.NE

The paper proposes a machine learning framework for rare disease detection, which involves learning patient patterns and generating candidate samples using generative adversarial networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of self-attentive and hierarchical embedding for patient pattern characterization suggests that the paper may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the use of adversarial training and max-margin classification suggests that the paper may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
